(39, 0, 1, 'devicon-apple-original colored', '/uploads/courses/ios.png', 'IOS App Development Training in Nepal', 'IOS App Development Training ', 'IOS App Development Training ', 'IOS Training in Nepal', 'iOS App Development Training in Kathmandu, Nepal', 'ios-app-development-training-in-nepal', 'iOS Training in Nepal | iOS App Development Training Institute in Kathmandu, Nepal', 'ios training in nepal, IOS Training in Kathmandu Nepal,  Iphone Training Nepal, swift Training Nepal, ios app development training in nepal', 'Take IOS Training at Broadway Infosys. Rated as Best IOS Training Institute in Kathmandu Nepal. Training by Industry Experts & 100% proficiency', '', 'iOS', '<h1>IOS App Development Training</h1>\r\n\r\n<h4>Developing Mobile Applications with iOS Platform</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>The application development process for iOS platforms (iPhone, iPad and future platforms) relies on a specialized paradigm of application development - the mobile paradigm.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Benefits of Courses</h4>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>iPhone Application Developer</li>\r\n	<li>iiOS Developer</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4>Why iOS</h4>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The Mobile App Paradigm</li>\r\n	<li>Introduction to Xcode</li>\r\n	<li>Main characteristics of mobile apps.</li>\r\n	<li>Differences between mobile apps and desktop apps</li>\r\n	<li>How iOS is tailored to a mobile platform.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4>Section 1: Introduction</h4>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Lecture 1 What Does The Course Cover?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4>Section 2: Getting Started</h4>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Lecture 2 Download and Install xcode</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 3 Frequently Asked Questions</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 4 How To Ask Great Questions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4>Section 3: Getting Started With Xcode 7 and Swift 2</h4>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Lecture 5 Introduction</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 6 Downloading &amp; Installing Xcode 7</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 7 Navigating The Xcode Interface</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 8 Adding Labels To Your Apps</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 9 Adding Labels To Your Apps (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 10 Working With Text Inputs &amp; Buttons</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 11 Working With Text Inputs &amp; Buttons (Xcode files)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 12 Running Some Code!</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 13 Running Some Code! (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 14 Making Apps Interactive</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Lecture 15 Making Apps Interactive (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 16 Your First App: Animal Ages</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 17 Your First App: Animal Ages (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 18 Section Summary</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4>Section 4: Swift 2 Deep Dive (Using Playgrounds)</h4>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Lecture 19 Introduction</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 20 The Swift 2 Playground</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 22 Working With Variables And Variable Types</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 23 Working With Variables And Variable Types (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 24 Working With Arrays And Dictionaries</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 26 Conditionals - If &amp; Else Statements</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 27 Conditionals - If &amp; Else Statements (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 28 Game: The Guessing Game</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 29 Game: The Guessing Game (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 30 Sequencing Your Code: For Loops</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 31 Sequencing Your Code: For Loops (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 32 Sequencing Your Code: While Loops</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 33 Sequencing Your Code: While Loops (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 34 App: Finding Primes - Part 1</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 35 App: Finding Primes - Part 1 (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 37 Creating Robust Layouts Using Constraints (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 39 App: Finding Primes - Part 2 (Xcode files)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 40 Section Summary</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4>Section 5: Advanced iOS Features: Timers, Tables, Permanent Storage &amp; Web Content</h4>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Lecture 41 5.0Introduction</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 42 Navigation &amp; Menu Bars With Bar Button Items</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 43 Navigation &amp; Menu Bars With Bar Button Items (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 44 App: Egg Timer With Navigation Bar</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 45 App: Egg Timer (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 46 Table Views &amp; Working With Classes</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 47 Table Views &amp; Working With Classes (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 48 App: Know Your Times Tables?</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 49 App: Know Your Times Tables? (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 50 Storing Data Permanently In Your Apps</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 51 Storing Data Permanently In Your Apps (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 52 Creating Multiple View Controllers &amp; Using Segues</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 53 Creating Multiple View Controllers &amp; Using Segues (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 54 Controlling The Keyboard With Taps &amp; The Enter Key</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 55 Controlling The Keyboard With Taps &amp; The Enter Key (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 56 App: What A To Do!</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 57 App: What A To Do! (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 58 Downloading Data From The Web</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 59 Downloading Data From The Web (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 60 Advanced String Manipulation &amp; Processing Web Data</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 61 Advanced String Manipulation &amp; Processing Web Data (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 62 App: Current Conditions</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 63 App: Current Conditions (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 64 Section Summary</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4>Section 6: Advanced iOS Features II: Animation, Games, Maps &amp; Geolocation, Audio</h4>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Lecture 65 6.0Introduction</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 66 Programatically Manipulating UIImages</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 67 Programatically Manipulating UIImages (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 68 Creating Advanced Animations</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 69 Creating Advanced Animations (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 70 Game: Noughts &amp; Crosses</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 71 Game: Noughts &amp; Crosses (Xcode files)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 72 Integrating Maps Into Your Apps</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 73 Integrating Maps Into Your Apps (Xcode files)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 74 Advanced Maps: Adding Pins &amp; Messages</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 75 Advanced Maps: Adding Pins &amp; Messages (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 76 Geolocation: Using The User&#39;s Location In Your Apps</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 77 Geolocation: Using The User&#39;s Location In Your Apps (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 79 App: Location Aware (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 80 Advanced Segues - Executing Code Before &amp; After Segues</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 81 Advanced Segues - Executing Code Before &amp; After Segues (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 82 App: Memorable Places</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 83 App:Memorable Places (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 84 Playing, Pausing &amp; Restarting Audio</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 85 Playing, Pausing &amp; Restarting Audio (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 86 App: Back To Bach</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 87 App: Back To Bach (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 88 Responding To User Swipes &amp; Shaking The iPhone</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 89 Responding To User Swipes &amp; Shaking The iPhone (Xcode files)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 90 App: Shake It, Baby</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 91 App: Shake It, Baby (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 92 SectionSummary</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4>Section 7: Core Data, Advanced Web Content, Json Data &amp; Webviews</h4>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Lecture 93 7.0Introduction</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 94 Working With Core Data</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 95 Working With Core Data (Xcode files)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 96 Advanced Core Data - Searching For Objects</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 97 Advanced Core Data - Searching For Objects (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 98 Downloading Images From The Web</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 99 Downloading Images From The Web (continued)</li>\r\n	<li>Lecture 100 Working With Json Data &amp; Dictionaries</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Prerequisites</strong><br />\r\nBasics of Programming Language.</p>\r\n', '<h2>IOS training in Nepal:</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Our iOS training curriculum provides career-oriented training to produce globally competent iOS developers. The training is solely focused for disseminating holistic knowledge of iOS ecosystem and iOS apps development to the students. As the numerous iOS based projects are outsourced to Nepalese developers from around the world there is a wider career scope for iOS developers in Nepal. Therefore, Broadway is committed to provide quality iOS training in Nepal.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Course highlights:</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The course includes basic introduction to iOS app development with swift, UIKit fundamentals, iOS networking with swift, iOS app deployment. The course includes all the essential topics required for becoming a basic iOS developer capable of developing apps for iPhones, iPads and so on. The trainees will have to undertake a project work to develop basic iOS application at the end of the course.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Benefits of iOS Training in Broadway Infosys Nepal:</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Availability of enough materials required for iOS training</li>\r\n	<li>Availability of highly qualified and experienced iOS instructors</li>\r\n	<li>Providing training on reasonable cost and offering scholarship for outstanding students</li>\r\n	<li>Regular interaction with experienced iOS trainers involved in developing advanced application worldwide</li>\r\n	<li>Best trainee support and development methodology</li>\r\n	<li>Extensive knowledge on implying iOS skills in work environment</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Syllabus outline:</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Objective C, memory management, iPhone SKD, interface builder, data storage, XML and web services, touches and gesture, multimedia, maps, working with storyboard, handling different screen sizes, multithreading, notification, using camera, accessing device sensors, mails and SMS, transitioning to the iPad, deployment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you want to develop your career as IOS developer, we will definitely provide the best training. We look forward to hear you anytime via email, online forms, our social media pages or any medium to reserve your seat for upcoming iOS training session.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, '<p>Basic Programming Concept (C /C++)</p>\r\n', '2 Months', '', '', '', '<h2><strong>iOS App Development with Swift 3&nbsp;</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>IOS Apps Development Courses<br />\r\n<br />\r\nCourses Outline:-&nbsp;iOS App Development Training&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>learn iOS 10 and swift 3&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\nSwift Fundamentals / Basic UIKit</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Introduction iOS / xCode / devices / Playground</li>\r\n	<li>Variables, Types, and Control Flow</li>\r\n	<li>Optional Types, Collections, Enums</li>\r\n	<li>Functions and Closures</li>\r\n	<li>Classes and Structures</li>\r\n	<li>Extensions / Property Observers</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Advance UIKit / Advance Swift</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Operators</li>\r\n	<li>Generics / Size Classes</li>\r\n	<li>Error Handling</li>\r\n	<li>Singletons</li>\r\n	<li>Operator Overloading</li>\r\n	<li>Protocol</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>AVFoundation</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Using Camera to take Pictures</li>\r\n	<li>Use Gallery to add pictures in projects.</li>\r\n	<li>Use Sound files</li>\r\n	<li>Record Audio</li>\r\n	<li>Record Video</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>View Controllers</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>UITableViewController</li>\r\n	<li>UICollectionViewController</li>\r\n	<li>UITabBarController</li>\r\n	<li>UINavigationController</li>\r\n	<li>UIPageViewController / Animation</li>\r\n	<li>App State</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Networking / Persistence</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>URLSession</li>\r\n	<li>Parsing JSON with NSJSONSerialization</li>\r\n	<li>Refactoring To Use HTTPGetRequest</li>\r\n	<li>User Defaults / UIDocument</li>\r\n	<li>Working with Files / NSKeyedArchiver</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Notification (Local / Remote), Using External Library</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>MapKit Framework</li>\r\n	<li>Push Notification / Local Notification</li>\r\n	<li>Gestures, Taps, and Touches / Timer</li>\r\n	<li>LocationKit</li>\r\n	<li>Third Party Dependancy (Cocoapod, Carthage)</li>\r\n	<li>Localization</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Extension Series</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Drawing / UIControl</li>\r\n	<li>Swift / Objective-C Interoperability</li>\r\n	<li>Version Control (git, bitbucket)</li>\r\n	<li>Code Quality</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Custom fonts / Images</li>\r\n	<li>Submitting to the App Store</li>\r\n	<li>Storyboards / UILabel / UIView / Outlet / IBAction</li>\r\n	<li>UITextField / UITextView</li>\r\n	<li>UIButton / UISegmentControl / UISwitch</li>\r\n	<li>UIScrollView / UISlider</li>\r\n	<li>UIWebView / UIStackView</li>\r\n	<li>UIAlertController</li>\r\n	<li>UIDatePicker / UIPickerView</li>\r\n	<li>Auto Layout / Access Control, Adaptive Layout</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Integrating Social Services:-</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Facebook</li>\r\n	<li>Twitter</li>\r\n	<li>Google</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Introduction to Game Framework (Intro Only)</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Scenekit</li>\r\n	<li>SpriteKit</li>\r\n	<li>Metal</li>\r\n	<li>Game Kit<br />\r\n	Submitting to the app store<br />\r\n	The Final Project</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 'iOS Developer', 'https://broadwayinfosys.com/iphone-ios-development-training-course-nepal.php', 6, '2017-06-22 12:41:55', 1),
(40, 0, 1, 'devicon-angularjs-plain colored', '/uploads/courses/AngularJS.png', 'AngularJS Training In Nepal', 'AngularJS Training', 'AngularJS', 'AngularJS Training in Nepal', '', 'angularjs-training-in-nepal', 'Angular JS Training in Nepal | Front End Javascript Training in Nepal', 'angular js training in nepal, front end javascript training in nepal', 'Angular JS training offers you an extensive learning edge to become a front end developer. Java script framework training for front end environment is a way to go for future technology.', '', 'AngularJS', '<h1>Angular.js</h1>\r\n', '<p>Angular JS is an open source web application framework that is primarily maintained by Google and its community of developers who share that the main idea behind introducing Angular JS is to cope with the challenges faced by Single Page Applications (web apps that load a single HTML page and update dynamically as users interact with the applications). Since the Single Page Applications are getting popular these days, Angular JS skills offer much for the developers in the future.</p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, '<p>&bull; Should be familiar with any one web development technologies&nbsp;<br />\r\n&bull; Should have intermediate level exposure in JavaScript</p>\r\n', '1.5 Months', 'Saturday, Sunday', '', '', '<h3>Introduction to AngularJS</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Single Page application(SPA) Vs Conventional Web Application</li>\r\n	<li>What does AngularJS do?</li>\r\n	<li>Who controls AngularJS?</li>\r\n	<li>How can I get AngularJS?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Anatomy of an AngularJS application</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Setup and Installation</li>\r\n	<li>Creating Boundaries using ng-app</li>\r\n	<li>Model View Controller(MVC) &amp; Model View View Model(MVVM)</li>\r\n	<li>Scope</li>\r\n	<li>Expressions</li>\r\n	<li>Modules</li>\r\n	<li>Templates and Data Binding</li>\r\n	<li>Repeating elements in templates</li>\r\n	<li>Angular Animations</li>\r\n	<li>Angular SQL</li>\r\n	<li>Routing and multiple views</li>\r\n	<li>Dependency injection</li>\r\n	<li>Using Expressions, CSS Classes and Styles</li>\r\n	<li>Using Controllers for UI responsibility separation</li>\r\n	<li>Responding to model changes</li>\r\n	<li>Making an API call</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>AngularJS building blocks</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Model</li>\r\n	<li>View</li>\r\n	<li>Controller</li>\r\n	<li>Directive</li>\r\n	<li>Filter</li>\r\n	<li>Services</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Model</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>How to create a model</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Controller</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Building a basic controller</li>\r\n	<li>Managing scope</li>\r\n	<li>Setting up behavior</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Views</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Creating a view</li>\r\n	<li>Tying a view to controller</li>\r\n	<li>Tying a view to model</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Using Filters</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Filters Overview</li>\r\n	<li>Understanding Filter Expressions</li>\r\n	<li>Building custom Filters</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Services</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Services Overview</li>\r\n	<li>Modularity using Services</li>\r\n	<li>Injecting Services</li>\r\n	<li>Factories</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Directives</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Directives Overview</li>\r\n	<li>Creating Directives</li>\r\n	<li>The Directive Definition Object</li>\r\n	<li>Compilation and Linking</li>\r\n	<li>Creating Components</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Form Validation</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Using the Form Element</li>\r\n	<li>Naming Inputs</li>\r\n	<li>Utilizing Form Properties</li>\r\n	<li>Dynamic Styles</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Communication with servers</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Communicating over $http</li>\r\n	<li>Configuring the requests</li>\r\n	<li>Sending Http Headers</li>\r\n	<li>Caching Responses</li>\r\n	<li>Request and Response Transformation</li>\r\n	<li>Using RESTful Resources</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Unit Testing(Optional)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Testing Models using Jasmine</li>\r\n	<li>Test considerations for Directives and Filters</li>\r\n	<li>Using Angular Mocks</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Project Work(Compulsory)</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A single page application using AngularJS and Web API</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', 'https://broadwayinfosys.com/angularjs-training-nepal.php', 39, '2017-05-18 12:56:57', 1),
