(93, 6, 0, '', '/uploads/courses/1487854994.png', 'Revit  Architecture Training in Nepal', 'Revit  Architecture Training', 'Revit  Architecture Training', 'Revit Architecture Training Nepal', 'Revit Architecture Training Nepal', 'revit-architecture-training-nepal', 'Revit Architecture Training in Nepal | Revit Architecture Design Training in Nepal', 'revit architecture training in nepal, revit architecture design training', 'Enroll into revit architecture training in Nepal. Become proficient in revit architecture design by learning with industry leading expert teachers.', '', NULL, NULL, '<p>Revit Architecture training offers courses on Building Information Model software for architecture design and modeling. The courses on Revit architecture are designed for architects, contractors, designers, civil engineers and other related professionals. Revit training is intended to provide understanding of important aspects of digital drawings and 3D models that provide guidance on designing various components of building digitally in a 3D view.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As Revit architecture is gaining popularity around the world for designing perfect building components and planning construction resources accordingly, the individuals that are trained in implementing building information model software are able to predict accurate quantities and cost of materials required for the construction of building.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They can do so digitally while estimating accurate budget for the overall construction. The training can benefit the architects and designers to design great prototypes and eliminate repetitive tasks of designing as Revit architecture facilitates for error-free and high quality construction documentations.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Why REVIT Training</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Popular Building Information Model Software for architecture design and modeling</li>\r\n	<li>Understanding of valuable aspects of digital drawings and 3D models</li>\r\n	<li>Useful tool to reap benefits of interconnected data in digital drawings</li>\r\n	<li>Best tool to design various components of a building in a 3D view</li>\r\n	<li>Prediction of accurate quantities and cost of materials possible</li>\r\n	<li>Most useful to contractors and owners for accurate budget estimation</li>\r\n	<li>Eliminates repetitive tasks of designing</li>\r\n	<li>Helpful for error-free and high quality construction documentations</li>\r\n	<li>Career opportunity as architecture designers, Revit instructor , 3D design experts and so on</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, '', '2 Months', '', '', '', '<h3>The Revit World</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The Revit Architecture Interface</li>\r\n	<li>The Revit Workflow</li>\r\n	<li>The Ribbon</li>\r\n	<li>The View Window</li>\r\n	<li>Object Selection</li>\r\n	<li>Modifying and Mirroring</li>\r\n	<li>Building on Existing Geometry</li>\r\n	<li>View Control and Object Display</li>\r\n	<li>The Project Browser</li>\r\n	<li>Windows</li>\r\n	<li>File Types and Families</li>\r\n	<li>System and Hosted Families (.rfa)</li>\r\n	<li>Using Revit Template File (.rte)</li>\r\n	<li>Using Revit Family Files (.rft)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Creating a Model</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Placing Walls</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Exterior Walls</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Interior Walls</li>\r\n	<li>Placing Interior Partitions</li>\r\n	<li>Editing Wall Joins</li>\r\n	<li>Placing Doors and Windows into Your Walls</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Doors</li>\r\n	<li>Placing Openings in Your Walls</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Windows</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Creating Views</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Creating Levels</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Levels</li>\r\n	<li>The Composition of a Level</li>\r\n	<li>Other Level Adjustments</li>\r\n	<li>Creating Building Sections</li>\r\n	<li>Making Building Modifications in a Section.</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Wall Sections</li>\r\n	<li>Creating Detail Sections</li>\r\n	<li>Modifying Ceiling Grids</li>\r\n	<li>Ceiling Element Properties</li>\r\n	<li>Creating a Custom Ceiling</li>\r\n	<li>Creating Ceiling Openings and Soffits</li>\r\n	<li>Creating a Ceiling Opening</li>\r\n	<li>Creating a Soffit</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Light Fixtures to Ceilings</li>\r\n	<li>Interior Design</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Plumbing Fixtures and Furniture</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Parabolic Troffers</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Casework and Furniture</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Alternate Floor Materials</li>\r\n	<li>Creating a Tile Material</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Stairs, Ramps, and Railings</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Creating Stairs Using the Rise/Run Function</li>\r\n	<li>Boundaries</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Railings</li>\r\n	<li>Creating a Winding Staircase</li>\r\n	<li>Making Railing Adjustments</li>\r\n	<li>Stair and Railing Families</li>\r\n	<li>Creating a Custom Railing System</li>\r\n	<li>Creating Custom Stairs</li>\r\n	<li>Adding a Custom Landing</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Ramps</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Schedules and Tags</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Creating Schedules</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Fields to a Schedule</li>\r\n	<li>Sorting and Grouping</li>\r\n	<li>Controlling Headers</li>\r\n	<li>Modifying Elements in a Schedule</li>\r\n	<li>Modifying the Schedule\'s Appearance</li>\r\n	<li>Creating Material Takeoffs</li>\r\n	<li>Creating a Calculated Value Field</li>\r\n	<li>Creating Key Legends</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Legend Components</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Symbols to a Legend</li>\r\n	<li>The Type Properties Dialog</li>\r\n	<li>Creating an Arched Door</li>\r\n	<li>Creating a 3D Extrusion Within a Family</li>\r\n	<li>Creating a 3D Sweep Within a Family</li>\r\n	<li>Creating an In-Place Family</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Site and Topography</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Adding a Site WithinRevi</li>\r\n	<li>Modifying a Toposurface</li>\r\n	<li>Splitting the Surface</li>\r\n	<li>Creating Subregions</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Site Components</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Contour Properties and Labels</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Building Pads to Displace Earth</li>\r\n	<li>Adding a Property Line</li>\r\n	<li>Creating a Toposurface by Instance</li>\r\n	<li>Creating a Graded Region</li>\r\n	<li>Orientating a Site</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Rendering and Presentation</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Creating an Exterior Rendering</li>\r\n	<li>Creating Lighting Groups</li>\r\n	<li>Interior Rendering</li>\r\n	<li>Creating Walkthroughs</li>\r\n	<li>Exporting an Animation</li>\r\n	<li>Creating a Solar Study</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Importing and Coordinating Revit Models</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Importing and Linking a Revit Structure Model.</li>\r\n	<li>Copy Monitor</li>\r\n	<li>Adjusting the Copy/Monitor Settings</li>\r\n	<li>Coordination Alert</li>\r\n	<li>Interference Detection</li>\r\n	<li>Importing and Exporting CAD Formats</li>\r\n	<li>Exporting a Model to CAD</li>\r\n	<li>Exporting a 2D Model</li>\r\n	<li>Exporting the Model to 3D CAD</li>\r\n	<li>Crop Regions</li>\r\n	<li>Splitting a Section Segment</li>\r\n	<li>Creating Callouts</li>\r\n	<li>Creating a Camera View</li>\r\n	<li>Modifying the Camera</li>\r\n	<li>Creating an Elevation</li>\r\n	<li>Interior Elevations</li>\r\n	<li>Elevation Properties</li>\r\n	<li>Annotation Properties</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Working with the Revit Tools</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The Edit Commands</li>\r\n	<li>The Move Command</li>\r\n	<li>The Copy Command</li>\r\n	<li>The Rotate Command</li>\r\n	<li>The Array Command</li>\r\n	<li>Radial Array</li>\r\n	<li>Linear Array</li>\r\n	<li>The Mirror Command</li>\r\n	<li>The Align Tool</li>\r\n	<li>Locking an Alignment</li>\r\n	<li>Split</li>\r\n	<li>Trim</li>\r\n	<li>Offset</li>\r\n	<li>Copy/Paste</li>\r\n	<li>Creating the Plans</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Dimensioning and Annotating</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Dimensioning</li>\r\n	<li>Aligned Dimensions</li>\r\n	<li>Linear Dimensions</li>\r\n	<li>Angular Dimensions</li>\r\n	<li>Radial Dimensions</li>\r\n	<li>Arc Length Dimensions</li>\r\n	<li>Using Dimensions as a Layout Tool</li>\r\n	<li>Constraining the Model</li>\r\n	<li>Using Dimensions to Move Objects</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Text</li>\r\n	<li>Importing AutoCAD Legends</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Tags</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Tags Individually</li>\r\n	<li>Using the Tag All Command</li>\r\n	<li>Tagging by Material</li>\r\n	<li>Creating Custom Tags</li>\r\n	<li>Multicategory Tags</li>\r\n	<li>Keynoting</li>\r\n	<li>Keynoting by Element</li>\r\n	<li>Keynoting by Material</li>\r\n	<li>Keynoting by User</li>\r\n	<li>Creating Keynote Legends</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Detailing</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Working with Line Weights</li>\r\n	<li>Drafting on Top of the Detail</li>\r\n	<li>Using Predefined Detail Components</li>\r\n	<li>Masking Regions</li>\r\n	<li>Repeating Details</li>\r\n	<li>Modifying a Detail Component</li>\r\n	<li>Modifying Filled Regions</li>\r\n	<li>Drawing Detail Lines</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Notes</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Notes by Material</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Textual Notation</li>\r\n	<li>Creating Blank Drafting Views</li>\r\n	<li>Creating a Detail Group</li>\r\n	<li>Adding a Section to Another View</li>\r\n	<li>Importing AutoCAD into a Drafting View</li>\r\n	<li>Adding 2D and 3D Lines to the Model</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Creating Specific Views and Match Lines</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Duplicating Views</li>\r\n	<li>Creating Dependent Views</li>\r\n	<li>Adjusting the Crop Regions</li>\r\n	<li>Adjusting the Annotation Crop Region</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Match Lines</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Phasing and Design Options</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Managing Project Phasing</li>\r\n	<li>Creating an Existing Phasing Plan</li>\r\n	<li>Demolishing Components</li>\r\n	<li>Creating a Demo Plan</li>\r\n	<li>Examining Phase Filters</li>\r\n	<li>Design Options</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Project Collaboration</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Enabling and Utilizing Worksharing</li>\r\n	<li>Enabling Worksets</li>\r\n	<li>Creating a Central Model</li>\r\n	<li>Creating a Local File</li>\r\n	<li>Working in the Revit Shared Environment</li>\r\n	<li>Loading or Not Loading a Workset</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>BIM Management</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Setting Up the Template</li>\r\n	<li>Managing Settings</li>\r\n	<li>Import/Export Settings</li>\r\n	<li>Controlling Annotations</li>\r\n	<li>Creating and Understanding Shared Parameters</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Leader Text</li>\r\n	<li>Changing the Leader Type</li>\r\n	<li>Modifying the Text Placement</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Floors</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Placing a Floor Slab</li>\r\n	<li>Sketching the Slab</li>\r\n	<li>Building a Floor by Layers</li>\r\n	<li>Adding a Layer</li>\r\n	<li>Splitting the Floor\'s Materials</li>\r\n	<li>Split and Paint</li>\r\n	<li>Pitching a Floor to a Floor Drain</li>\r\n	<li>Creating Shaft Openings</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Roofs</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Placing Roofs by Footprint</li>\r\n	<li>Flat Roofs by Footprint</li>\r\n	<li>Pitched Roofs by Footprint</li>\r\n	<li>Creating a Sloping Roof</li>\r\n	<li>Roofs by Extrusion</li>\r\n	<li>Adding a Roof Dormer</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Structural Items</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Structural Grids</li>\r\n	<li>Placing a Grid</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Structural Columns</li>\r\n	<li>Structural Framing</li>\r\n	<li>Adding a Beam System</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Bracing</li>\r\n	<li>Foundation Systems</li>\r\n	<li>Foundation Walls</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Structural Footings</li>\r\n	<li>Structural Slabs</li>\r\n	<li>Piers and Spread Footings</li>\r\n	<li>Structural Views</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Ceilings and Interiors</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Creating Ceilings</li>\r\n	<li>Match Line Appearance</li>\r\n	<li>Using View Templates</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Creating Sheets and Printing</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Creating and Populating Sheets</li>\r\n	<li>Sheet Organization</li>\r\n	<li>Modifying a Viewport</li>\r\n	<li>Viewport Element Properties</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Revisions to a Sheet</li>\r\n	<li>Addressing Project Parameters</li>\r\n	<li>Generating a Cover Sheet</li>\r\n	<li>Printing from Revit Architecture</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Creating Rooms and Area Plans</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Creating Rooms</li>\r\n	<li>Configuring Element Properties</li>\r\n	<li>Placing and Manipulating Room Tags</li>\r\n	<li>Adding a Room Schedule</li>\r\n	<li>Adding a Color Fill Plan</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Room Separators</li>\r\n	<li>Creating an Area Plan</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Advanced Wall Topics</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Creating Compound Walls</li>\r\n	<li>Adding \"Layers\" to the Compound Wall</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Wall Sweeps</li>\r\n	<li>Modifying a Wall\'s Profi le In-Place</li>\r\n	<li>Manually Adding Host Sweeps</li>\r\n	<li>Creating Stacked Walls</li>\r\n	<li>Creating Curtain Walls</li>\r\n	<li>Adding a Predefined Curtain Wall</li>\r\n	<li>Adding a Blank Curtain Wall</li>\r\n	<li>Creating Curtain Grids</li>\r\n	<li>Adding a Wall to a Massing Object</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Creating Families</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Creating a Basic Family</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Reference Planes to a Family</li>\r\n	<li>Adding Dimensions and Parameters to a Family</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 'Revit Designer', NULL, 99, '2017-06-11 11:36:33', 1),
(94, 6, 0, '', '/uploads/courses/1487855885.png', 'Google Sketchup Training in Nepal', 'Google Sketchup Training', 'Google Sketchup Training', 'Google Sketchup Training in Nepal', '', 'google-sketchup-training-in-nepal', 'Google Sketchup Training in Nepal | Google Sketchup Training Institute in Kathmandu, Nepal', 'google sketch up training in nepal, Google sketchup 3D modeling', 'Enroll into Google Sketchup training at Broadway Infosys Nepal. Become proficient expert in 3D modeling. Learn with industry leading expert teachers.', '', NULL, NULL, '<p>The training course on Sketchup is primarily targeted at professional designer and architects in architecture, engineering and construction industry. However, any individual with keen interest in designing buildings and other structures digitally can pursue Sketchup training to develop and enhance their professional design skills. The sketchup training course offers the understanding and skills of 3D designing for architecture, construction, engineering, urban planning, 3D printing, game design, event stage design, interior design etc. Thus, Sketchup has got wider scope that is enough to allure the individuals to pursue career in professional designing using digital resources</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Why Sketchup Training</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Sketchup provides one of the world’s largest libraries of 3D models</li>\r\n	<li>You don’t have to design everything from scratch</li>\r\n	<li>There are various add-ons available to customize your 3D designs</li>\r\n	<li>You can upload your 3D designs in Sketchup’s 3D warehouse and earn global recognition</li>\r\n	<li>You get to learn how to build complex construction using simple components</li>\r\n	<li>Round the clock community support from professional designers in construction, architecture, engineering and entertainment industry</li>\r\n	<li>Earning opportunity by offering and implementing Sketchup expertise to delight clients</li>\r\n	<li>Wider career scope as Sketchup training enhances your design skills in multiple domains</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, '', '1 Month ', '', '', '', '<h3>The sketchup Interface</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Interface basics</li>\r\n	<li>Navigating in sketchup</li>\r\n	<li>Walking around in sketchup</li>\r\n	<li>Creating camera views</li>\r\n	<li>Shading faces and edges</li>\r\n	<li>Creating shadows and fog</li>\r\n	<li>Creating scenes</li>\r\n	<li>Selecting and moving objects</li>\r\n	<li>Scaling and rotating</li>\r\n	<li>Manipulating faces and edges</li>\r\n	<li>Advanced selection tools</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Drawing in sketchup</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Line tool</li>\r\n	<li>Using line tool for 3d</li>\r\n	<li>Rectangle tool</li>\r\n	<li>Circles and polygons</li>\r\n	<li>Arcs</li>\r\n	<li>Pull/push</li>\r\n	<li>Offset</li>\r\n	<li>Follow me</li>\r\n	<li>Text/3d text</li>\r\n	<li>Softening round edges</li>\r\n	<li>Construction tools</li>\r\n	<li>sections</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Organizing scenes</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Grouping objects</li>\r\n	<li>Creating components</li>\r\n	<li>Working with layers</li>\r\n	<li>Creating layers</li>\r\n	<li>Outliners</li>\r\n	<li>Hiding and unhiding</li>\r\n	<li>Locking and unlocking</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Creating textures and materials</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Applying materials</li>\r\n	<li>Editing materials</li>\r\n	<li>Creating materials</li>\r\n	<li>Mapping materials</li>\r\n	<li>Applying bitmap image</li>\r\n	<li>Mapping curved objects</li>\r\n	<li>Projecting maps</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Google SketchUp Designer ', NULL, 100, '2017-06-11 11:38:22', 1),
(95, 4, 1, '', '/uploads/courses/1487842278.png', 'SQL DBA Training in Nepal', 'SQL DBA Training', 'SQL DBA Training', 'SQL DBA Training In Nepal', 'SQL Training in Nepal', 'sql-dba-training-in-nepal', 'SQL DBA  Training in Nepal | SQL DBA Training Institute in Nepal', 'sql dba training in Nepal, sql dba institute in nepal', 'Take SQL DBA Training at Broadway Infosys. Rated as Best SQL server training Institute in Kathmandu Nepal. Training by Industry Experts & 100% proficiency.', '', NULL, NULL, '<h2>SQL DBA Training in Nepal</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>As Database Administrators play a significant role in IT companies their global demand is ever increasing. Thus, we have designed special training courses for individuals willing to pursue SQL DBA training in Nepal. The SQL DBA training aims to groom the database management skills of database administrators, SQL Developers, Database Engineers and so on.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Course Highlights</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Basic understanding of SQL Relational Database Management and its environment</li>\r\n	<li>Understanding SQL Server Relational Engine, Integration Services, Reporting and Analysis Services</li>\r\n	<li>Learn data migration and disaster recovery solutions</li>\r\n	<li>Understand query tuning, replication management and high availability</li>\r\n	<li>Overall capacity building in MSSQL database management</li>\r\n	<li>Real time Project work to test SQL DBA skills</li>\r\n	<li>SQL DBA Certification exam</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Benefits of SQL DBA Training at Broadway Infosys Nepal</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Certified SQL experts as instructors</li>\r\n	<li>Well equipped training labs</li>\r\n	<li>Support for placement for deserving trainees</li>\r\n	<li>Interactive and participative classes</li>\r\n	<li>Flexible timing</li>\r\n	<li>Supervision of project work by instructors and industry experts</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Syllabus Outline</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Introduction to MSSQL Server 2016</li>\r\n	<li>MSSQL Server 2016 installation</li>\r\n	<li>Understanding SQL Server 2016 Infrastructure Management Environment</li>\r\n	<li>Perform MSSQL server database design</li>\r\n	<li>Microsoft SQL Database Security</li>\r\n	<li>SQL Database Backup and Recovery</li>\r\n	<li>Performing database upgrades and maintenance</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>We are excited to hear from aspiring Database developers like you via web, social media or direct phone call. Please make sure you reserve your seat for upcoming SQL DBA training session as there is high competition to secure the seats.</p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, '', '2 Months', '', '', '', '<h3><strong>SQL Server Database Administrator - DBA</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nCourses Outline:-SQL Server DBA</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>Introduction to database management systems and databases</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>What is a database and a database management system (DBMS?)</li>\r\n	<li>Introduction to Microsoft SQL Server and its overall SQL Server Data Platform</li>\r\n	<li>History and Current trends of DBMS and Database Administration Tasks of a Database Administrator</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>SQL Server 2016&nbsp;Installation</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Editions of SQL Server 2016</li>\r\n	<li>Hardware and Software pre-requisites for a successful SQL Server installation.</li>\r\n	<li>Understanding SQL Server components.</li>\r\n	<li>Perform a successful SQL Server 2016&nbsp;installation</li>\r\n	<li>Slipstreaming SQL Server installation with service packs.</li>\r\n	<li>Understanding SQL Server version identifiers, installed directories and conventions.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>SQL Server 2016&nbsp;Administration and Development Tools</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Using SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS)</li>\r\n	<li>Using SQL Server Command Line interface</li>\r\n	<li>Using SQL Server Configuration Manager</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>SQL Server 2016&nbsp;Architecture</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Understanding SQL Server system databases.</li>\r\n	<li>Understanding the SQL Server database structure.</li>\r\n	<li>SQL Server files and filegroups.</li>\r\n	<li>SQL Server Transactional logs, Recovery Models.</li>\r\n	<li>What is the difference between SQL Server instance and database.</li>\r\n	<li>Client-Server Communication.</li>\r\n	<li>Attaching and detaching SQL Server databases.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>SQL Server Database objects</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Understanding Schemas</li>\r\n	<li>Understanding SQL Server data types</li>\r\n	<li>Understanding column properties</li>\r\n	<li>Creating tables, altering tables and adding constraints, relationships.</li>\r\n	<li>Understanding the filter</li>\r\n	<li>Creating database diagrams</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Understanding Locks &amp; their Usage</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>SP_WHO2 and SP_LOCK Outputs</li>\r\n	<li>Lock Types, Lock Hints and Lock Escalations</li>\r\n	<li>Avoiding WAITS on PAGE and TABLE</li>\r\n	<li>Isolation Levels - Types and Usage</li>\r\n	<li>READ COMMITED and SERIALIZABLE</li>\r\n	<li>READ UNCOMMITED and REAPEATABLE</li>\r\n	<li>SNAPSHOT &amp; READCOMITTED SNAPSHOT</li>\r\n	<li>Choosing Isolation Levels For OLTP</li>\r\n	<li>Statement Locks &amp; Transaction Locks</li>\r\n	<li>TempDB Issues with Isolation Options</li>\r\n	<li>Locking Hints to Avoid Blockings</li>\r\n	<li>A DEADLOCK Scenario and DML Audits</li>\r\n	<li>Deadlock Detection and Avoidance</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>SQL Server Backup and Recovery &ndash; Part 1</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Introduction to Backup and Recovery strategy for databases.</li>\r\n	<li>Full Database backups using SIMPLE Recovery Model</li>\r\n	<li>Full Database and Transactional log backups with FULL Recovery Model</li>\r\n	<li>Backup history and maintenance</li>\r\n	<li>Designing Maintenance plans for Backup Tasks</li>\r\n	<li>SQL Server Agent for scheduling backups</li>\r\n	<li>Database Mail for email notifications to DBAs.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>SQL Server Backup and Recovery &ndash; Part 2</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Introduction to Database Restore and Recovery</li>\r\n	<li>Full database restore</li>\r\n	<li>Full database restore and recovery of transactional logs</li>\r\n	<li>Restoring system databases</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>SQL Server Data Export and Import (Data Movement)</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Partial Data export and import using GUI tools&ndash; Export and Import Wizard</li>\r\n	<li>Move or copy a full database.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>SQL Server security</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>SQL Server authentication vs. Windows authentication</li>\r\n	<li>Auditing database logins using SQL Server Error Logging</li>\r\n	<li>SQL Server server-wide logins and database specific users</li>\r\n	<li>Creating user-defined server roles</li>\r\n	<li>Configuring contained databases.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Performance Tuning&ndash; Part 1</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Understanding database indexes</li>\r\n	<li>Checking index fragmentation and maintaining them</li>\r\n	<li>Database statistics</li>\r\n	<li>Understanding SQL Server Profiler</li>\r\n	<li>Creating Traces</li>\r\n	<li>Running server-side traces</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Performance Tuning &ndash; Part 2</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Understanding the Extended Events architecture</li>\r\n	<li>Creating and configuring an Extended Events session</li>\r\n	<li>Using an extended events session to monitor system performance</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>SQL Server High Availability (Advance Topics)</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Database Mirroring</li>\r\n	<li>Log Shipping</li>\r\n	<li>AlwaysOn</li>\r\n	<li>Failover cluster instance improvements</li>\r\n	<li>Creating AlwaysOn availability groups</li>\r\n	<li>Administering AlwaysOn Availability groups</li>\r\n	<li>Reading secondary database copies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Data Exports (SSIS) and DB Mail</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Import &amp; Export Operations</li>\r\n	<li>OLE-DB, SQLNCLI and Jet Drivers</li>\r\n	<li>Choosing correct Data Providers</li>\r\n	<li>Scheduling SSIS Packages using Jobs</li>\r\n	<li>Proxies and Reading Job History</li>\r\n	<li>Database Scripting and DB Encryption</li>\r\n	<li>Database Cloning Process and Options</li>\r\n	<li>Configuring Linked Servers - Custom</li>\r\n	<li>SQL Server Agent - Alert Properties</li>\r\n	<li>Database (DB) Mail Configurations</li>\r\n	<li>Securing DB Profiles : SMTP Accounts</li>\r\n	<li>DB Mail Profiles and Public Tokens</li>\r\n	<li>Alert System Configurations in SQL Agent</li>\r\n	<li>Creating Operators and Emails</li>\r\n	<li>Warnings and Emails with DB Mail</li>\r\n	<li>Testing Job Failures and Notifications</li>\r\n	<li>Job Activity Monitor and History Delete</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 'Database Administrator', NULL, 69, '2017-06-12 13:25:46', 1),
