View Model</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Views</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>View Engines</li>\r\n	<li>Diferent types of Views</li>\r\n	<li>Introduction to Razor Syntax</li>\r\n	<li>Creating Layout Views</li>\r\n	<li>Creating Partial Views</li>\r\n	<li>Html Helpers</li>\r\n	<li>Uploading files</li>\r\n	<li>Form Handling</li>\r\n	<li>Creating Custom Html Helpers</li>\r\n	<li>Using thirdparty grid for displaying data</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Validation</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Client Side Validation</li>\r\n	<li>Server Side Validation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>AJAX and ASP.NET MVC</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>AJAX Helpers</li>\r\n	<li>CRUD operation using ASP.NET Ajax</li>\r\n	<li>Autocompletion</li>\r\n	<li>Paging Results</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>State Management</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Client Based State Management including Cookies, View Data, View Bag and Temp Data</li>\r\n	<li>Server Based State Management Including Session</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Globalization and Localization</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Globalization Using Resource</li>\r\n	<li>Globalization Using XML Resource</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>MVC Application Development Approach</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Developing and Migrating application using Code First</li>\r\n	<li>Developing application using Database First Approach</li>\r\n	<li>Scaffolding in ASP.NET MVC</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Security</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Authentication and Authorization</li>\r\n	<li>OWIN and Katana</li>\r\n	<li>XSRF/CSRF Prevention</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Performance</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Profile and Debug application with Glimpse</li>\r\n	<li>Using Asynchronous Methods</li>\r\n	<li>Bundling and Minification</li>\r\n	<li>Caching</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Design Patterns</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Creations Patterns including Singleton and Factory Method</li>\r\n	<li>Repository Pattern</li>\r\n	<li>Unit of Work Pattern</li>\r\n	<li>Using above patterns developing MVC application.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Email</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Send Email With CC And BCC</li>\r\n	<li>Send Email With Attachment</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Troubleshooting and Error Handling</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Debugging in Asp.NET MVC</li>\r\n	<li>Error Handling in ASP.NET MVC</li>\r\n	<li>Error Logging using ELMAH</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Configuring and Deploying -ASP.NET MVC Applications</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Configuring IIS and the .NET Framework</li>\r\n	<li>Deploying ASP.NET MVC Applications</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Reporting</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Incorporating ASP.NET MVC and SQL Server Reporting Service</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>WEB API</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Introduction</li>\r\n	<li>Patients and Data</li>\r\n	<li>Query by ID</li>\r\n	<li>Attribute Routing</li>\r\n	<li>IHttpActionResult</li>\r\n	<li>Cross Origin Resource Sharing</li>\r\n	<li>Authentication and Authorization</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Test Driven Development</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Introduction</li>\r\n	<li>UML</li>\r\n	<li>Unit Testing using NUnit</li>\r\n	<li>Test Driven Development</li>\r\n	<li>Test Driven Design</li>\r\n	<li>Testing Controllers</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 'Dot Net Developer', NULL, 67, '2017-04-25 08:54:44', 1),
(97, 10, 1, 'devicon-safari-plain colored', NULL, 'Digital Marketing Training in Nepal', 'Digital Marketing Training ', 'Digital Marketing Training ', 'Digital Marketing Training in Nepal', 'SEO, Analytics, Email Marketing & SEM Training in Kathmandu, Nepal', 'digital-marketing-training-seo-sem-smm-email', 'Digital Marketing & SEO Training in Nepal | SEO, SEM, SMM, PPC & Email Marketing Training', 'digital marketing training in nepal, seo training in nepal, sem training in nepal, ppc training in nepal, email marketing training in nepal', 'Enroll into digital marketing training for the advanced learning of online marketing. Explore new opportunities for your online presence technically as well as creatively. ', '', NULL, NULL, '<p><strong>Broadway Infosys Nepal,</strong> considering the need of modern marketing practices in the global market through the social and digital media, has lunched the Digital Marketing Training Course to update the marketing professionals and develop their confidence in fronting challenges occurring in the present marketing scenario. Driven with the philosophy of marketing, our course has focused on continue growth of rapid business promotion. Since marketers have to confront with various challenges and opportunities on this digital age, this course is designed to enhance the marketing professionals&#39; ability to face the challenges and go ahead. Our professional experts in the area of Digital Marketing would encourage the learners to be acquainted with the Online Marketing Challenges and help them to develop the better strategy for the global competition.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Digital Marketing is the modern method of business promotion, unlike the traditional form of marketing, through the practice of latest digital technologies and electronic media that mainly includes internet, websites, displaying boards, wireless devices, text messaging, mobile applications, digital televisions, podcasts, electronic billboards, radio channels, and so on. Digital marketing enables the organization to analyze whether the marketing campaign launched is effectively working or not in the real time. Digital marketing is being widely popular in the present world scenario as it provides a great platform to enhance the marketing plans for business promotion through the use of digital technologies without the physical presence. Digital marketing personnel can be associated with the different variables and can monitor them on the real time whether the content is working or not, what should be focused on, what is being searched, what is being viewed, how long the visitors being stayed, what conversations were done and much more.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Different techniques are in practice in digital marketing for instance <a href=\"https://broadwayinfosys.com/digital-marketing/seo/advanced-seo-training-in-nepal\">SEO</a> (Search engine Optimization), E-commerce marketing, SEM (Search Engine Marketing), content automation, boosting on social media, social media optimization, content marketing, e-mail marketing, display advertisement, SMS through mobile phones, blog articles etc. As a whole Digital marketing refers to advertising methods that are delivered through digital channels to the consumers. Our course moves round the periphery of the above mentioned aspects.</p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, '', '1.5 Months', '', '', '', '<h3>Introduction</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>What is Digital Marketing?</li>\r\n	<li>Latest Digital marketing trends</li>\r\n	<li>Digital Marketing strategy for websites</li>\r\n	<li>Online technicalities</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Search Engine Optimization</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Introduction to SEO</li>\r\n	<li>Technical SEO</li>\r\n	<li>Search Engine Algorithms and Updates</li>\r\n	<li>Google Webmasters Tools</li>\r\n	<li>Keyword Research Process</li>\r\n	<li>Competition Analysis</li>\r\n	<li>On page Optimization strategies</li>\r\n	<li>Off Page Optimization strategies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Search Engine Marketing</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Introduction to SEM (Paid Marketing)</li>\r\n	<li>PPC Overview</li>\r\n	<li>Google Adwords overview</li>\r\n	<li>Keywords Research &amp; setup</li>\r\n	<li>Bidding strategies</li>\r\n	<li>Dynamic search campaigns</li>\r\n	<li>Display Ads Campaigns</li>\r\n	<li>Remarketing campaigns</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Social Media Marketing</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Introduction to social media marketing</li>\r\n	<li>Social Media Platforms</li>\r\n	<li>Facebook, Twitter, Linkedin, Google+ &amp; Youtube overview</li>\r\n	<li>Social Media Organic Marketing</li>\r\n	<li>Social Media Advertising</li>\r\n	<li>Social Media for SEO</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Email Marketing</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Introduction to Email Marketing</li>\r\n	<li>Building email marketing strategy</li>\r\n	<li>Email Marketing Softwares</li>\r\n	<li>Mailchimp Overview</li>\r\n	<li>Building subscriber lists</li>\r\n	<li>Designing Newsletters</li>\r\n	<li>Campains Set Up</li>\r\n	<li>Reports and analysis</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Web Analytics</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Introduction to Web Analytics</li>\r\n	<li>Tools for website analytics</li>\r\n	<li>Installing Google Analytics in website</li>\r\n	<li>Basic terminology and KPI&rsquo;s</li>\r\n	<li>Reporting and Analysis</li>\r\n	<li>Conversion tracking &amp; Optimization</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', NULL, 80, '2017-05-25 15:03:19', 1),
(98, 12, 1, '', NULL, 'Tally Training in Nepal', 'Tally Training', 'Tally Training', 'Tally Training in Nepal', '', 'tally-training-in-nepal-1', 'Tally Training in Nepal | Tally Accounting Software Training Institute in Kathmandu Nepal', 'tally training in nepal, tally accounting training in nepal', 'Enroll and get in depth knowledge of tally, the renowned accounting software. Become professional accountant able to handle accounts technically', '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', NULL, '', '1Month', '', '', '', '<h1>Tally.ERP9</h1>\r\n\r\n<h3>Company Info</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Create/Modify/Delete Company</li>\r\n	<li>Change password</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Account Info</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Create/Modify/Delete Account Group</li>\r\n	<li>Create/Modify/Delete Account Ledger</li>\r\n	<li>Inventory Info</li>\r\n	<li>Create Simple/Compound Unit of Measure</li>\r\n	<li>Create/Modify/Delete Stock Group</li>\r\n	<li>Create/Modify/Delete Sock Item</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Voucher Entry (Trade Business)</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Purchase/Sales</li>\r\n	<li>Receipt/Payment</li>\r\n	<li>Contra</li>\r\n	<li>Journal</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Return Voucher</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Purchase/Sales Return</li>\r\n	<li>Other Return</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Order Processing</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Purchase Order/Receipt Note</li>\r\n	<li>Sales Order/Delivery Note</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>POS Invoice</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>Voucher Entry (Manufacturing)</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Purchase Raw Material</li>\r\n	<li>Finished Goods Products (BOM)</li>\r\n	<li>Sales</li>\r\n	<li>Multi Price Level (Wholesaler/Retailer)</li>\r\n	<li>Go down Transfer</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Voucher Entry (Medical Store)</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Batch, Mfg., Expire Date</li>\r\n	<li>Purchase/Sales</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Voucher Entry (Other)</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Multi-Currency</li>\r\n	<li>Cost Centers</li>\r\n	<li>Interest Calculation</li>\r\n	<li>Actual and Billed quantity</li>\r\n	<li>Separate Discount col