(12, 'Gaurav Jayasawal', 'jgaurav6@gmail.com', '9971847753', '9971847753', 'Android Development', 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/gaurav-jayasawal-7a85a8135/', '/uploads/instructor/1492284568.doc', 'I am a final year bachelor student at Amity University India and have a CGPA of 9.7/10 which makes me the topper of my batch of 31 students (I have documents to prove this). I did my primary, secondary as well as A Levels from Rato Bangala School, Nepal. I have an excellent command English as well as Nepali communication skills. I want to teach Android Development, amateur or advanced at IT Training Nepal. I will be able to take classes anytime from June 2017 as from this date I will have completed my bachelor of science in Information Technology. I have taken Android course twice from IT Training Nepal (beginner and advanced) over the course of 2 years. The reason for me doing the course twice is my determination to grab everything I could from my instructor as he was very knowledgeable in Android. I have a Microsoft (MTA) Software Development Fundamentals certification from Microsoft which shows my passion in coding and application development. This is the certificate that I received. (https://www.youracclaim.com/badges/27731332-271b-444f-857b-53751792e7a8/linked_in).\r\n\r\nOver the past 2 and half years, I have learned Android at an incredible pace and have knowledge in wide areas of it. I have done a few college projects as well as other personal projects. My programming and android knowledge can be depicted very clearly through my resume where I have included Git links to my projects. I have attached my CV in this email for your reference. I have taught in many schools as community service during my A Level studies and even before that, teaching individually and in groups were done at large in my school. In Amity University, since I am the batch topper, I am often a teacher to many peers and classmates. \r\n\r\nBeing a young Android enthusiast I am aware and up to date on the latest Android technologies and releases. I am very good at giving presentations and have been very active in such events since my school days till now. I can deliver my subject and my content with full clarity and can definitely teach in the best way. I am even starting my own tutorial series of Android in youtube soon. I will include this in my resume as soon as I complete doing this after my exam pressure is over within the next month. I think that if I\'m given a chance, I can prove what a great teacher I can be. Please do consider me if anything opens up. I am going to be back in Nepal on the 1st of June and I am free anytime after that. ', '2017-04-15 13:44:28', '2017-04-15 13:44:28'),
(13, 'Manohar Khadka', 'khadkamanohar@gmail.com', '9849604410', '9849604410', 'Php,CakePHP,MySQL,Codeigniter,Jquery,Bootstrap', '', '/uploads/instructor/1492693588.pdf', 'Currently I am working as web developer on oneplatinum technology (outsourcing company for australia) form last two years. And I am very interested to share my knowledge specially for any level of php training on project basis as well. I am available for 6:00 - 8:30 am in the morning. Waiting for the quick response.', '2017-04-20 07:21:28', '2017-04-20 07:21:28'),
(14, 'Laxmi Purbey', 'laxmipurbey.vis@gmail.com', '9819802573', '9819802573', 'iOS Developer / Instructor', 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/laxmi-purbey-1349a174?trk=nav_responsive_tab_profile', '/uploads/instructor/1493259396.docx', 'Since 2013, I have served as a Sr. IOS Developer for E-Signature ,New It Venture, Vis and Bidhee Pvt Ltd. where I have been repeatedly recognized for developing innovative solutions for multimillion-dollar. I am responsible for full lifecycle development of next-generation software, from initial requirement gathering to design, coding, testing, documentation and implementation. \r\n\r\nMy technical expertise includes cross-platform proficiency (Windows, Linux,Mac); fluency in 5 scripting/programming languages (including C, C++, Java, PHP and SQL,Swift,Objective C); and advanced knowledge of developer applications, tools, methodologies and best practices (including OOD, client/server architecture and self-test automation).\r\n\r\nMy experience developing user-friendly solutions on time and on budget would enable me to step into a software engineering role atE-Signature ,New It Venture, Vis and Bidhee Pvt  Ltd. and hit the ground running. For further information about me \r\nyou can find me on linked account as well \r\n\r\n\r\nI have also attached my latest resume along with this email.I look forward to speaking with you.\r\n', '2017-04-26 20:31:36', '2017-04-26 20:31:36'),
